<section id="writingtask1">
	<p class="popuptext">You should spend about 20 minutes on this task.</p>
  
  <p class="popuptext"><b>You live next to a large hotel. The hotel's rubbish bins are kept directly below your bedroom window and this is causing you problems.</b></p>

  <p class="popuptext"><b>Write a letter to the hotel. Explain how you are being affected by this situation and say what you would like them to do about it.</b></p>
  
  <p class="popuptext">You should write at least 150 words.</p>
  
  <p class="popuptext">You do&#xA0;<b>NOT</b>&#xA0;need to write your own address.</p>
  
  <p class="popuptext">Begin your letter as follows:</p>
  
  <p class="popuptext">Dear Sir/Madam,</p>

</section>

<section id="examtips">

<p class="popuptext">Letters of complaint are often organised into three paragraphs: a short introductory paragraph stating the nature of the complaint, a longer paragraph giving details and another short paragraph saying what you think should be done.</p>
